@springcoil @hayd for the first failing test (`test_cumcount_empty`, https://github.com/pydata/pandas/blob/master/pandas/tests/test_groupby.py#L3691). I think a one liner would be:

```
ge = DataFrame().groupby(level=0)
```

@hayd @jreback I think it is no problem to change the test here? As I don't see any reason that a `groupby` without arguments should work on an empty DataFrame (`DataFrame().groupby()`), but fails on a non-empty (`DataFrame(randn(3,3)).groupby()`)
